text: Trojanus of SaintesTrofianus, Trophianus. (died c.530) was a 6th century bishop of Saintes, in France. He is a Catholic saint, also known as Trojan and Troyen. His feast day is held on 30 November.Catholic Online page. ==References== Category:Christian saints Category:French Roman Catholics Category:Year of birth unknown Category:530 deaths
